; Coverage for report.cc line 728: fn_get_at index out of bounds on sequence
; When get_at is called on a sequence with an index >= sequence size,
; it returns void instead of throwing (changed for issue #697).

~ Monthly
    Expenses:Food    $200.00
    Assets:Checking

2024/01/15 Grocery
    Expenses:Food    $180.00
    Assets:Checking

test budget --begin 2024/01/01 --end 2024/02/01 --format '%(get_at(amount, 5))\n' Expenses
end test
